\pard\plain \tx1123\tx1685\tx2246\tx2794\tx3355\tx3917\tx4478\tx5040\tx5602\tx6163\tx6725\fi720\ri-720\sl288\slmult1\ql\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 It was the middle of night when they reached the end of the Tib. Everyone but Ayram was ecstatic. Ayram\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s fretful eye studied the north. \u8220\'93Looking for Hrks,\u8221\'94 he said.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 They might have made it out of the Tib, but they hadn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t made it out of danger. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Still, the mood was good, and doubly so, because the eastern rim of the world was peaked with the red Goree mountains. Those mountains had arrived all at once overnight, a long, dark, dumpy line, like some charge of cavalry meant to relieve the weary troops.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The way to those mountains was flat, an iron-red clay. The mountains themselves were brilliant bulwarks against the desert wind, and as such their faces bore the scars of the wind\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s assault.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Ayram led them south in line with these mountains, towards the Goree Pass.}
